author: nighfeckindroom1989

resources.description:
Mel Kiper's latest "Big Board" and Todd McShay's Draft Board still rate Stanford QB Andrew Luck, despite his off-game against Oregon.
No surprise there, really.
Here's what McShay said about Luck's standing:Luck hit a speed bump last week with a pair of interceptions -- including one returned for a touchdown -- in a loss to Oregon, but he remains the most complete quarterback prospect in years and is in no danger of losing the top spot on the board.And Kiper:Coming off his worst game of the season, but I still think he's really unable to show off all he can do given the talent around him. He's the total package. Arm strength, size, smarts, demeanor. Still a safe bet to be No. 1 overall.As for the rest of the Pac-12 on their draft boards, Kiper goes like this:1. Luck2. Matt Kalil, OT, USC7. Jonathan Martin, OT, Stanford10. Matt Barkley, QB, USC15. Vontaze Burfict, LB, Arizona State
And McShay:
1. Luck2. Kalil8. Martin11. Barkley15. Burfict17. David DeCastro, OG, Stanford
